With a sluggish growth and unemployment stubbornly high at just over 27%, the newly appointed ministers and their deputies have vowed to turn the economy around. The over 60 national executives were sworn-in by Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng and his deputy Raymond Zondo at the Sefako Makgatho Presidential Guesthouse in Pretoria. The reduced executive also comprised of young people with a fifty-fifty gender representation. New faces include Deputy Finance Minister David Masondo, who said his key priority will be to work to attract investment and stimulate job creation.  